description: phunction.sh house rules (Rust/WASM audiovisual instrument)
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

Read AGENTS.md first — it is the canonical map and the non-negotiables.
Condensed here:

- Build ONLY through `just` (`just dev`, `just build`, `just check`). The
  justfile owns the threaded-wasm rustflags; bare cargo/trunk wasm builds
  produce broken artifacts.
- `just check` must be green before any push; pushes to main deploy to
  production.
- Audio thread code (`phazor-core::Engine::process` and below): no
  allocation, no locks, no strings, no unbounded work. UI↔engine
  communication is Copy PODs over rtrb rings only.
- Musical time comes from the Transport frame counter; events are
  frame-offset within the render quantum. Never wall-clock.
- Ship the debugger: tracing/meters/error surfaces stay in production.
- New dependencies go through docs/crates-policy.md (verify version,
  maintenance, wasm32 support — don't trust training memory).
- wgpu and leptos break APIs every release: check the vendored source in
  the cargo registry or docs before writing against them.
- Public items get doc comments stating invariants/why (missing_docs=warn).
